Sin is crouching at the door, eager to control you. But you must subdue it and be its master.”"}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door. Its desire is contrary to you, but you must rule over it.”"}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"If you do what is right, will you not be accepted? But if you refuse to do what is right, sin is crouching at your door; it desires you, but you must master it.”"}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"\"If you do well, will not your countenance be lifted up? And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door; and its desire is for you, but you must master it.\""}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin lies at the door. And its desire "}, {:version=>" for you, but you should rule over it.”", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. And unto thee ", :text=>" his desire, and thou shalt rule over him."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"If you do what is right, won't you be accepted? But if you do not do what is right, sin is crouching at the door. Its desire is for you, but you must rule over it.\""}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"If you had done the right thing, you would be smiling. But you did the wrong thing, and now sin is waiting to attack you like a lion. Sin wants to destroy you, but don't let it! "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"If you had done the right thing, you would be smiling; but because you have done evil, sin is crouching at your door. It wants to rule you, but you must overcome it.\" "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"If you do what is right, won't you be accepted? But if you do not do what is right, sin is crouching at the door. Its desire is for you, but you must rule over it.\" "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"If you do what is appropriate, you'll be accepted, won't you? But if you don't do what is appropriate, sin is crouching near your doorway, turning toward you. Now as for you, will you take dominion over it?\" "}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"Is it not true that if you do what is right, you will be fine? But if you do not do what is right, sin is crouching at the door. It desires to dominate you, but you must subdue it.\" "}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"If you do well, will it not be lifted up? If you do not do well, sin lies in wait at the door. It desires to control you, but you must rule over it.\""}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"If you do well, won't you be accepted? But if you don't do well, sin is lying outside your door ready to attack. It wants to control you, but you must master it.\""}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"If thou doest well, shall it not be lifted up? and if thou doest not well, sin coucheth at the door; and unto thee is its desire, but thou mayest rule over it.'"}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"“If you do well, will not "}, {:version=>" be lifted up? And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door; and its desire is for you, but you must master it.”", :text=>"King James 2000 Bible"}, {:version=>"If you do well, shall you not be accepted? and if you do not well, sin lies at the door. And you shall be its desire, and you must rule over it.", :text=>"American King James Version"}, {:version=>"If you do well, shall you not be accepted? and if you do not well, sin lies at the door. And to you shall be his desire, and you shall rule over him.", :text=>"American Standard Version"}, {:version=>"If thou doest well, shall it not be lifted up? and if thou doest not well, sin coucheth at the door: and unto thee shall be its desire, but do thou rule over it.", :text=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation"}, {:version=>"Hast thou not sinned if thou hast brought it rightly, but not rightly divided it? be still, to thee shall be his submission, and thou shalt rule over him.", :text=>"Douay-Rheims Bible"}, {:version=>"If thou do well, shalt thou not receive? but if ill, shall not sin forthwith be present at the door? but the lust thereof shall be under thee, and thou shalt have dominion over it. ", :text=>"Darby Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"If thou doest well, will not [thy countenance] look up [with confidence]? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door; and unto thee [shall be] his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.", :text=>"English Revised Version"}, {:version=>"If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin coucheth at the door: and unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.", :text=>"Webster's Bible Translation"}, {:version=>"If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. And to thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.", :text=>"World English Bible"}, {:version=>"If you do well, will it not be lifted up? If you don't do well, sin crouches at the door. Its desire is for you, but you are to rule over it.\"", :text=>"Young's Literal Translation"}, {:version=>" Is there not, if thou dost well, acceptance? and if thou dost not well, at the opening a sin-offering is crouching, and unto thee its desire, and thou rulest over it.'", :text=>nil}]}